6:
Nope, no way. I don't believe it for a
second.
7:
We're talking about Regis here! No
way he's the lead in a heartwarming
story like this, nuh-uh.
11:
Now that you mention it, I guess
there WAS something... odd about
him the whole time.
13: I wonder what his endgame is?
17:
I dunno about endgame, but I'm
pretty sure he's got something
going on with the merchants of
Palpebra.
22:
See! There it is! I knew it. That
no-good droid is up to something
sneaky!
25:
Hmm... We should look into this. Let's
follow him!
28: F-follow him? You sure about that?
31:
Yep, absolutely. Someone needs to
teach him what it means to have
your privacy invaded!
34: Sounds like this is personal for you...
47:
Ohhh, he is just SO suspicious.
Everything about him screams he's
up to no good. And what's with the
white outfit, anyway? Is he going to
a wedding?!
52:
My, my. Trying to pin false
accusations on moi, are you?
55:
Dia, my dear. You're really not suited
for the work of a private eye, you
know that?
56:
I can read you like a book—even
without this remote bit to spy on you.
62:
Wh-what?! No way, you had shared
optical sensors installed on your
bits?!
66:
Isn't that technically a neural
expansion?! Those are ILLEGAL, you
know!
69:
Rules, my dear, are meant to be
broken. Besides, who's going to
enforce them now that the
Administrator's gone?
73:
That aside, if you have such a keen
interest in my personal enterprise,
why not come along with me and
see for yourself?
74:
This matter concerns all of you, after
all.
80:
Did you grow these by yourself,
Regis?
83:
Not quite. I replanted them—though
I did go through quite an ordeal
getting them here in such a short
time.
87:
White flowers. She did say she liked
those.
93: I think I'll pass. I've been already.
96:
Plus, there are things you can't talk
about around me, right? It's better
that I wasn't there.
103:
Sorry, you two, but would you be
willing to keep Regis company for
this? It's hard for him to do this on
his own. He gets blue.
115:
I would indeed be most grateful if
you joined me, mes amis!
120: We're supposed to just pick a flower?
124:
Not just one—as many as you can
hold in your hands!
130: Oh, I see... This is her grave.
134:
That's right. Despite what you might
think, we too have beliefs
surrounding the spirits and souls of
the dead.
138:
Real flowers haven't grown on our
planet for a long time—not since the
day fire rained from the sky.
140:
So I had to bring real ones from
elsewhere—secretly borrowing the
World Flipper to do so, of course.
142:
This was actually the "enterprise" I
was talking about. I plan to sell
flowers to androids. Not a bad idea,
right?
150:
Hmm. Who knows... Can you really
say that you loved someone who
you hated, blamed, and even killed?
153:
Someone once told me that we are
free to interpret what "love" means
to us.
158:
Hahaha. Touché, my dear! You're
right.
161:
It's just difficult for me to be honest
about my feelings.
167:
We should get going. If we don't get
back soon, our little canary is likely
to give us quite the chirping!
